#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:1.1.0"
msgid "75. Talasattikasikkhāpada"
msgstr ""
"<hgroup><h1 id=\"Bu-Pc.75\">Monks’ Confession 75: the training rule on "
"threatening with the palm of the hand</h1></hgroup>"

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli4.147
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:1.1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"nidana\">Origin story</h2><p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.75.1\""
">Bu-Pc.75.1</a><a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.3.49\">BD.3.49</a><a class"
"=\"wt-pa\">1356</a>At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the "
"Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:1.1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū kupitā anattamanā "
"sattarasavaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ talasattikaṃ uggiranti."
msgstr ""
"At that time the monks from the group of six <a class=\"pts-vp-pi\" id=\""
"Vin.4.147\">Vin.4.147</a> raised their hand in anger against the monks from "
"the group of seventeen."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:1.1.3"
msgid "Te pahārasamuccitā rodanti."
msgstr "Expecting to be struck, they cried."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:1.1.4"
msgid "Bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "Other monks asked them why,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:1.1.5"
msgid "“kissa tumhe, āvuso, rodathā”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:1.1.6"
msgid ""
"“Ime, āvuso, chabbaggiyā bhikkhū kupitā anattamanā amhākaṃ talasattikaṃ "
"uggirantī”ti."
msgstr "and they told them what had happened.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:1.1.7"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1357</a>The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:1.1.8"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:1.1.9"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū kupitā anattamanā sattarasavaggiyānaṃ "
"bhikkhūnaṃ talasattikaṃ uggirissantī”ti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"“How can the monks from the group of six raise their hand in anger against "
"the monks from the group of seventeen?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:1.1.10"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, kupitā anattamanā sattarasavaggiyānaṃ "
"bhikkhūnaṃ talasattikaṃ uggirathā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:1.1.11"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:1.1.12"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:1.1.13"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, kupitā anattamanā sattarasavaggiyānaṃ "
"bhikkhūnaṃ talasattikaṃ uggirissatha."
msgstr ""
"Foolish men, how can you raise your hand in anger against the monks from the "
"group of seventeen?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:1.1.14"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:1.1.15"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="rule">
#. REF: sc3
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:1.1.16"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhussa kupito anattamano talasattikaṃ uggireyya, "
"pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"pannatti\">Final ruling</h2><p class=\"rule\"><a class=\"pts-vp-en\""
" id=\"BD.3.50\">BD.3.50</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1358</a>‘If a monk raises a "
"hand in anger against another monk, he commits an offense entailing "
"confession.’”</p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc4
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"pada\">Definitions</h2><p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.75.2\""
"></a><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.75.2.1\">Bu-Pc.75.2.1</a><a class=\"wt-"
"pa\">1359</a><term>A</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "<gloss>whoever …</gloss>"

#. HTML: </b><b class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "<term>Monk</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:2.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "<gloss>…"

#. HTML: </b>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:2.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr ""
"The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through "
"a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this "
"case.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:2.1.6"
msgid "Bhikkhussāti"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1360</a><term>Against another monk</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:2.1.7"
msgid "aññassa bhikkhussa."
msgstr "<gloss>against a different monk.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:2.1.8"
msgid "Kupito anattamanoti"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1361</a><term>In anger</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:2.1.9"
msgid "anabhiraddho āhatacitto khilajāto."
msgstr "<gloss>discontent, having hatred, hostile.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:2.1.10"
msgid "Talasattikaṃ uggireyyāti"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1362</a><term>Raises a hand</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:2.1.11"
msgid ""
"kāyaṃ vā kāyapaṭibaddhaṃ vā antamaso uppalapattampi uccāreti, āpatti "
"pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"<gloss>if he raises the body or something connected to his body, even if "
"only a lotus leaf, he commits an offense entailing confession.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p>
#. REF: sc8
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:2.2.1"
msgid ""
"Upasampanne upasampannasaññī kupito anattamano talasattikaṃ uggirati, āpatti "
"pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"cakka\">Permutations</h2><p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.75.2.2\""
">Bu-Pc.75.2.2</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1363</a>If it is one who is fully "
"ordained, and he perceives him as fully ordained, and he raises a hand "
"against him in anger, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:2.2.2"
msgid ""
"Upasampanne vematiko kupito anattamano talasattikaṃ uggirati, āpatti "
"pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is one who is fully ordained, but he is unsure if he is, and he raises "
"a hand against him in anger, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:2.2.3"
msgid ""
"Upasampanne anupasampannasaññī kupito anattamano talasattikaṃ uggirati, "
"āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is one who is fully ordained, but he does not perceive him as fully "
"ordained, and he raises a hand against him in anger, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:2.2.4"
msgid ""
"Anupasampannassa kupito anattamano talasattikaṃ uggirati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1364</a>If he raises a hand in anger against one who "
"is not fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:2.2.5"
msgid "Anupasampanne upasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is one who is not fully ordained, but he perceives him as fully "
"ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:2.2.6"
msgid "Anupasampanne vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is one who is not fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, he commits "
"an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:2.2.7"
msgid "Anupasampanne anupasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is one who is not fully ordained, and he does not perceive him as "
"fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:2.2.8"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"anapatti\">Non-offenses</h2><p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1365</a>There is "
"no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:2.2.9"
msgid ""
"kenaci viheṭhīyamāno mokkhādhippāyo talasattikaṃ uggirati, ummattakassa, "
"ādikammikassāti."
msgstr ""
"if he is being oppressed and he raises a hand for the purpose of freeing "
"himself; if he is insane; if he is the first offender.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc75:2.2.10"
msgid "Talasattikasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
"<hr><p class=\"endsutta\"><a class=\"wt-pa\">1366</a>The fifth rule, the "
"training rule on threatening with the palm of the hand, is finished.</p>"
